    • genresMenu

      public static String genresMenu()
      Creates a string of Movie genres in the format: 
           0: science fiction
     1: fantasy
     2: drama
    ...
    10: mystery
      Note the alignment of the genre numbers.
      Returns:
      a formatted numbered string of Movie genres.

    • compareTo

      public int compareTo(Movie target)
      Movies are compared by title, then by year if the titles match. Must ignore case. Ex: {Zulu, 1964} precedes {Zulu, 2013}. Returns:
      • 0 if this equals target
      • < 0 if this precedes target
      • > 0 if this follows target
      Specified by:
      compareTo in interface Comparable<Movie>

    • write

      public void write(PrintStream ps)
      Writes a single line of movie data to an open PrintStream in the format: 
       "title|year|director|rating|genre"
      The quote character (") is not part of the string. See the file movies.txt for an example of the file format and contents.
      Parameters:
      ps - output PrintStream
